Arcadia Papers: ABSTRACT</H1>
<HR>

<A HREF="ftp://liege.ics.uci.edu/pub/arcadia/papers/djr/spec-based-tav.ps.gz">
"<b>Approaches to Specification-Based Testing</b>"</A>,
by Debra J. Richardson, Owen O'Malley and Cindy Tittle in
<i>Proceedings of the Third ACM SIGSOFT Symposium on Software Testing,
Analysis and Verification,</i>
pages 86-96, Keywest, December 1989.

<H2> Abstract </H2>

Current software testing practices focus, almost exclusively, on the 
implementation, despite widely acknowledged benefits of testing based 
on software specifications. We propose approaches to specification-based 
testing by extending a wide variety of implementation-based testing
techniques to be applicable to formal specification languages. We 
demonstrate these approaches for the Anna and Larch specification languages. 

